Ooh, it works on my system with exactly the same configuration when I do not open the project via a directory junction.

Context: I use a junction at `~\projects\Windows` which points to `~\.projects_local`. I.e. `~\projects\Windows\windows-reports` is actually at `~\.projects_local\windows-reports`. When opening `~\.projects_local\windows-reports` in VS Code (i.e. without junction), podman can actually build the container. But when opening `~\projects\Windows\windows-reports` (i.e. with junction), podman fails with the error message from above.

@virzak do you also have a directory junction in your project path? or do we have different issues altogether?
